Some of South Africa's top academics and researchers based at UWC will discuss and showcase their work at the 2018 Research Week. Other topics include nanoelectrochemistry, waste pickers and health activism. Deputy vice-chancellor for Research and Innovation at UWC Professor Josè Frantz said Research Week was an opportunity to celebrate, discuss and explore diverse ideas and collaborations at the university. “This is an opportunity to showcase the importance of research and how it is used in all facets of life. "Research and innovation are multidimensional processes that involve different actors, and at UWC we aim to make research count for communities,” said Frantz. The event will be hosted at the School of Public Health at UWC from tomorrow until Friday. Staff Writer